New Records: Victor Wembanyama achieved a rare 5×5 (five of each category) with 25 points, nine rebounds, seven assists, five blocks and five steals.
Key Match Events: San Antonio forced Utah into 12 turnovers in the third quarter while seizing momentum.
The Spurs outscored the Jazz 30-14 in the period, turning a six-point halftime deficit into a 77-67 lead going into the final quarter.
Post-Match Reflections: The Jazz, who shot 39 percent, are the only winless team remaining in the NBA.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Victor Wembanyama joined Hakeem Olajuwon and Andrei Kirilenko as the only NBA players ever to accomplish the 5×5 more than once.
Harrison Barnes scored six points for the Spurs in a 16-2 run to open the second half.
Others: Utah started two rookies because of injuries.
Kyle Filipowski had 12 points and five rebounds, filling in for Markkanen, while Cody Williams, the 10th overall draft pick, scored two points and secured five rebounds.
